<td class="answercell">
    <div class="post-text"><p>You can always customize how <code>bundle</code> installs by passing an argument to the installer:</p>

<pre><code>bundle install --path /some/path
</code></pre>

<p>This is useful for the case you highlight, or in cases where a shared directory will be used by different platforms or Ruby versions.</p>

<p><strong>Update</strong>:</p>

<p>It should be possible to re-position the <code>~/.bundler</code> directory by setting your <code>$HOME</code> environment variable to be something that will work, which in effect alters what <code>~</code> interprets as. Bundler appears to use the method <code>Gem.user_home</code> method to determine where to put this file, so if you can fake that out you are set.</p>

<p>This could be as simple as:</p>

<pre><code>HOME=/some/home bundle install --path /some/path
</code></pre>
</div>
    <table class="fw">
